## Key Learning Points

### Authentication Enumeration

Authentication systems can reveal information about valid users through different responses.

### User Enumeration

An attacker may identify valid usernames by observing application behavior.

### Verbose Errors

Detailed error messages can leak sensitive information and help attackers enumerate users.

### Password Reset Logic

Weak password reset implementations can introduce account takeover risks.

### HTTP Basic Authentication

Understanding how HTTP Basic Authentication works and common security concerns.

### OSINT

Open Source Intelligence can help attackers gather information before targeting systems.

## Security Recommendations

- Use generic authentication error messages.
- Implement rate limiting.
- Enforce strong password policies.
- Secure password reset mechanisms.
- Monitor brute-force attempts.

## Lessons Learned

This room improved my understanding of authentication attacks, user enumeration techniques, and common weaknesses in login systems.
